<HL>
   Securities Markets to Close
   Early Today for Christmas
</HL>
<DATE>
12/24/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE 17
</SO>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- U.S. securities markets generally will close
early today for Christmas Eve and will be closed tomorrow.
   The New York Stock Exchange and American Stock Exchange
will close at 2 p.m. EST, and the Public Securities
Association has recommended that the U.S. government
securities market close at the same time.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The Pacific Stock Exchange will close trading in equities
and options activities between 2:10 p.m. and 2:30 p.m. EST
today.
   In Canada, banks, exchanges, government offices and most
businesses will be closed Tuesday and Wednesday for the
Christmas and Boxing Day holidays. There won't be any mail
delivery.
</TEXT>
